{{also|Yer|YER|'yĕr|ýer|-yer|þér}}
==English==
===Etymology 1===
Most likely from the [[intrusive r|intrusive R]], between "yeah" (/jəː/) and a non-high vowel (/ə/, /ɪə/, /ɑː/, /ɔː/). For example, "Yeah-r-I know" (/jəɹ ʌɪ nəʊ/)
====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|en|/jə(ɹ)/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-yer.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|ə(ɹ)|s=1}}
====Adverb====
{{en-adv|?}}
# {{lb|en|UK|slang|or|dialectal}} {{pronunciation spelling of|en|yeah|nodot=11}}, [[yes]].
===Etymology 2===
